    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>We cant vote on who control a company. But still they take to their power to dictate over us. Who we should be allowed to give our own money to or not.</p> 
<p>You might not like Wikileaks today. But you might like it tomorrow, but by than it might be to late.</p> 
<p>We cant allways trust government to have the right opinion as history have showed over and over again, bad governments happen from time to time. And if we can not give our own money to whoever we like we are prisoners.</p> 
<p>Bitcoin is freedom outside a prison dictated by a few people you and I do not know and can not chose.</p> 
<p>But someone might send money to “terrorists”. There is no reason to be afraid of terrorists. Terrorism kills less people than almost anything in the world. Skin cancer, car accidents, aids, cancer, heart diseases, sugar.</p> 
<p>Americans Are as Likely to Be Killed by Their Own Furniture as by Terrorism</p> 
<p>Of 978 terrorism-related kidnapping last year, only three hostages were private U.S. citizens</p> 
<p>According to the report, the number of U.S. citizens who died in terrorist attacks increased by two between 2010 and 2011; overall, a comparable number of Americans are crushed to death by their televisions or furniture each year.</p> 
<p>http://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2012/06/americans-are-as-likely-to-be-killed-by-their-own-furniture-as-by-terrorism/258156/</p> 
<p>But the newspapers do not report on everyone who died from other stuff and interview their friend and family. It just doesnt make headlines.</p> 
<p>If the papers did, they would be filled with deaths and people would go mad for the governments to put more into preventing the things that people really die from.</p> 
<p>Not more into survailling their own people. Those who they are elected to serve.</p>

    	</div>



