    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>I decide how I spend my money and I decide what organizations to support – no one else. I resent that MasterCard &amp; VISA, companies that I’ve held accounts with for 20+ years, have caved in to the government’s demands rather than putting their customers first. I applaud WikiLeaks for continuously finding ways to “Beat the Blockade.” I have every intention of helping them win this battle by donating to them regularly. I do think it’s disheartening that there is not greater understanding by the public of how this blockade violates all our rights. I suspect, however, that should the day come that Macy’s or Walmart are added to the blockade, you’ll hear a lot more screaming from consumers.</p>

