    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>I’ve taken advantage of the many ways it’s still possible to financially support wikileaks (methods outlined on the WL pages) despite the US government’s attempts to censor it. Bitcoin and direct paper checks drawn on US banks work fine, and take only a little patience &amp; application to set up.</p> 
<p>I think it’s also important to boycott paypal and the credit-card issuers &amp; banks that have joined in the censorship without any protest. There is indeed life without paypal or ebay, and there are alternative credit-card issuers and banks which (even if only by grace of the gods or accident of fate) haven’t yet been drawn into the government’s assault on free speech and responsible citizenship.</p>

